rafael campo cultural competence page 1 stanford arts humanities and medicine program presents a reading by rafael campo cultural competence poetry and the importance of voice in the illness experience dr campo is associate professor of medicine harvard medical school and director office of multicultural affairs and the humanism in medicine program the author of seven books of essays and poetry his awards include the agni poetry prize the national poetry series open competition award two lambda literary awards poetry and biography autobiography and finalist national book critic circle award his clinical work includes aids medicine he holds a joint stanford humanities center sica fellowship for arts writers practitioners nominated by the arts humanities and medicine program stanford center for biomedical ethics thursday march 1 2012 6 30 pm cantor arts center auditorium stanford university free and open to the public seating is limited no reservations
